33// We don't pull the RTP constants from rtputils.h, to avoid a layer violation.
34static const size_t kDtlsRecordHeaderLen = 13;
35static const size_t kMaxDtlsPacketLen = 2048;
36static const size_t kMinRtpPacketLen = 12;
37
38// Maximum number of pending packets in the queue. Packets are read immediately
39// after they have been written, so a capacity of "1" is sufficient.
40//
41// However, this bug seems to indicate that's not the case: crbug.com/1063834
42// So, temporarily increasing it to 2 to see if that makes a difference.
43static const size_t kMaxPendingPackets = 2;
44
45// Minimum and maximum values for the initial DTLS handshake timeout. We'll pick
46// an initial timeout based on ICE RTT estimates, but clamp it to this range.
47static const int kMinHandshakeTimeout = 50;
48static const int kMaxHandshakeTimeout = 3000;
49
50static bool IsDtlsPacket(const char* data, size_t len) {
51 const uint8_t* u = reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(data);
52 return (len >= kDtlsRecordHeaderLen && (u[0] > 19 && u[0] < 64));
53}
54static bool IsDtlsClientHelloPacket(const char* data, size_t len) {
55 if (!IsDtlsPacket(data, len)) {
56 return false;
57 }
58 const uint8_t* u = reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(data);
59 return len > 17 && u[0] == 22 && u[13] == 1;
60}
61static bool IsRtpPacket(const char* data, size_t len) {
62 const uint8_t* u = reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(data);
63 return (len >= kMinRtpPacketLen && (u[0] & 0xC0) == 0x80);
64}

66StreamInterfaceChannel::StreamInterfaceChannel(
67 IceTransportInternal* ice_transport)
68 : ice_transport_(ice_transport),
69 state_(rtc::SS_OPEN),
70 packets_(kMaxPendingPackets, kMaxDtlsPacketLen) {}
71
72rtc::StreamResult StreamInterfaceChannel::Read(void* buffer,
73 size_t buffer_len,
74 size_t* read,
75 int* error) {
76 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&sequence_checker_);
77
78 if (state_ == rtc::SS_CLOSED)
79 return rtc::SR_EOS;
80 if (state_ == rtc::SS_OPENING)
81 return rtc::SR_BLOCK;
82
83 if (!packets_.ReadFront(buffer, buffer_len, read)) {
84 return rtc::SR_BLOCK;
85 }
86
87 return rtc::SR_SUCCESS;
88}
89
90rtc::StreamResult StreamInterfaceChannel::Write(const void* data,
91 size_t data_len,
92 size_t* written,
93 int* error) {
94 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&sequence_checker_);
95 // Always succeeds, since this is an unreliable transport anyway.
96 // TODO(zhihuang): Should this block if ice_transport_'s temporarily
97 // unwritable?
98 rtc::PacketOptions packet_options;
99 ice_transport_->SendPacket(static_cast<const char*>(data), data_len,
100 packet_options);
101 if (written) {
102 *written = data_len;
103 }
104 return rtc::SR_SUCCESS;
105}
106
107bool StreamInterfaceChannel::OnPacketReceived(const char* data, size_t size) {
108 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&sequence_checker_);
109 if (packets_.size() > 0) {
110 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Packet already in queue.";
111 }
112 bool ret = packets_.WriteBack(data, size, NULL);
113 if (!ret) {
114 // Somehow we received another packet before the SSLStreamAdapter read the
115 // previous one out of our temporary buffer. In this case, we'll log an
116 // error and still signal the read event, hoping that it will read the
117 // packet currently in packets_.
118 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to write packet to queue.";
119 }
120 SignalEvent(this, rtc::SE_READ, 0);
121 return ret;
122}
123
124rtc::StreamState StreamInterfaceChannel::GetState() const {
125 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&sequence_checker_);
126 return state_;
127}
128
129void StreamInterfaceChannel::Close() {
130 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&sequence_checker_);
131 packets_.Clear();
132 state_ = rtc::SS_CLOSED;
133}

167bool DtlsTransport::SetLocalCertificate(
168 const rtc::scoped_refptr<rtc::RTCCertificate>& certificate) {
169 if (dtls_active_) {
170 if (certificate == local_certificate_) {
171 // This may happen during renegotiation.
172 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << ToString() << ": Ignoring identical DTLS identity";
173 return true;
174 } else {
175 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << ToString()
176 << ": Can't change DTLS local identity in this state";
177 return false;
178 }
179 }
180
181 if (certificate) {
182 local_certificate_ = certificate;
183 dtls_active_ = true;
184 } else {
185 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << ToString()
186 << ": NULL DTLS identity supplied. Not doing DTLS";
187 }
188
189 return true;
190}
191
192rtc::scoped_refptr<rtc::RTCCertificate> DtlsTransport::GetLocalCertificate()
193 const {
194 return local_certificate_;
195}

197bool DtlsTransport::SetDtlsRole(rtc::SSLRole role) {
198 if (dtls_) {
199 RTC_DCHECK(dtls_role_);
200 if (*dtls_role_ != role) {
201 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR)
202 << "SSL Role can't be reversed after the session is setup.";
203 return false;
204 }
205 return true;
206 }
207
208 dtls_role_ = role;
209 return true;
210}
211
212bool DtlsTransport::GetDtlsRole(rtc::SSLRole* role) const {
213 if (!dtls_role_) {
214 return false;
215 }
216 *role = *dtls_role_;
217 return true;
218}

228bool DtlsTransport::SetRemoteFingerprint(const std::string& digest_alg,
229 const uint8_t* digest,
230 size_t digest_len) {
231 rtc::Buffer remote_fingerprint_value(digest, digest_len);
232
233 // Once we have the local certificate, the same remote fingerprint can be set
234 // multiple times.
235 if (dtls_active_ && remote_fingerprint_value_ == remote_fingerprint_value &&
236 !digest_alg.empty()) {
237 // This may happen during renegotiation.
238 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << ToString()
239 << ": Ignoring identical remote DTLS fingerprint";
240 return true;
241 }
242
243 // If the other side doesn't support DTLS, turn off |dtls_active_|.
244 // TODO(deadbeef): Remove this. It's dangerous, because it relies on higher
245 // level code to ensure DTLS is actually used, but there are tests that
246 // depend on it, for the case where an m= section is rejected. In that case
247 // SetRemoteFingerprint shouldn't even be called though.
248 if (digest_alg.empty()) {
249 RTC_DCHECK(!digest_len);
250 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << ToString() << ": Other side didn't support DTLS.";
251 dtls_active_ = false;
252 return true;
253 }
254
255 // Otherwise, we must have a local certificate before setting remote
256 // fingerprint.
257 if (!dtls_active_) {
258 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << ToString()
259 << ": Can't set DTLS remote settings in this state.";
260 return false;
261 }
262
263 // At this point we know we are doing DTLS
264 bool fingerprint_changing = remote_fingerprint_value_.size() > 0u;
265 remote_fingerprint_value_ = std::move(remote_fingerprint_value);
266 remote_fingerprint_algorithm_ = digest_alg;
267
268 if (dtls_ && !fingerprint_changing) {
269 // This can occur if DTLS is set up before a remote fingerprint is
270 // received. For instance, if we set up DTLS due to receiving an early
271 // ClientHello.
272 rtc::SSLPeerCertificateDigestError err;
273 if (!dtls_->SetPeerCertificateDigest(
274 remote_fingerprint_algorithm_,
275 reinterpret_cast<unsigned char*>(remote_fingerprint_value_.data()),
276 remote_fingerprint_value_.size(), &err)) {
277 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << ToString()
278 << ": Couldn't set DTLS certificate digest.";
279 set_dtls_state(DTLS_TRANSPORT_FAILED);
280 // If the error is "verification failed", don't return false, because
281 // this means the fingerprint was formatted correctly but didn't match
282 // the certificate from the DTLS handshake. Thus the DTLS state should go
283 // to "failed", but SetRemoteDescription shouldn't fail.
284 return err == rtc::SSLPeerCertificateDigestError::VERIFICATION_FAILED;
285 }
286 return true;
287 }
288
289 // If the fingerprint is changing, we'll tear down the DTLS association and
290 // create a new one, resetting our state.
291 if (dtls_ && fingerprint_changing) {
292 dtls_.reset(nullptr);
293 set_dtls_state(DTLS_TRANSPORT_NEW);
294 set_writable(false);
295 }
296
297 if (!SetupDtls()) {
298 set_dtls_state(DTLS_TRANSPORT_FAILED);
299 return false;
300 }
301
302 return true;
303}

305std::unique_ptr<rtc::SSLCertChain> DtlsTransport::GetRemoteSSLCertChain()

307 if (!dtls_) {
308 return nullptr;
309 }

325
326bool DtlsTransport::SetupDtls() {
327 RTC_DCHECK(dtls_role_);
328 {
329 auto downward = std::make_unique<StreamInterfaceChannel>(ice_transport_);
330 StreamInterfaceChannel* downward_ptr = downward.get();
331
332 dtls_ = rtc::SSLStreamAdapter::Create(std::move(downward));
333 if (!dtls_) {
334 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << ToString() << ": Failed to create DTLS adapter.";
335 return false;
336 }
337 downward_ = downward_ptr;
338 }
339
340 dtls_->SetIdentity(local_certificate_->identity()->Clone());
341 dtls_->SetMode(rtc::SSL_MODE_DTLS);
342 dtls_->SetMaxProtocolVersion(ssl_max_version_);
343 dtls_->SetServerRole(*dtls_role_);
344 dtls_->SignalEvent.connect(this, &DtlsTransport::OnDtlsEvent);
345 dtls_->SignalSSLHandshakeError.connect(this,
346 &DtlsTransport::OnDtlsHandshakeError);
347 if (remote_fingerprint_value_.size() &&
348 !dtls_->SetPeerCertificateDigest(
349 remote_fingerprint_algorithm_,
350 reinterpret_cast<unsigned char*>(remote_fingerprint_value_.data()),
351 remote_fingerprint_value_.size())) {
352 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << ToString()
353 << ": Couldn't set DTLS certificate digest.";
354 return false;
355 }
356
357 // Set up DTLS-SRTP, if it's been enabled.
358 if (!srtp_ciphers_.empty()) {
359 if (!dtls_->SetDtlsSrtpCryptoSuites(srtp_ciphers_)) {
360 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << ToString() << ": Couldn't set DTLS-SRTP ciphers.";
361 return false;
362 }
363 } else {
364 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << ToString() << ": Not using DTLS-SRTP.";
365 }
366
367 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << ToString() << ": DTLS setup complete.";
368
369 // If the underlying ice_transport is already writable at this point, we may
370 // be able to start DTLS right away.
371 MaybeStartDtls();
372 return true;
373}

391// Called from upper layers to send a media packet.
392int DtlsTransport::SendPacket(const char* data,
393 size_t size,
394 const rtc::PacketOptions& options,
395 int flags) {
396 if (!dtls_active_) {
397 // Not doing DTLS.
398 return ice_transport_->SendPacket(data, size, options);
399 }
400
401 switch (dtls_state()) {
402 case DTLS_TRANSPORT_NEW:
403 // Can't send data until the connection is active.
404 // TODO(ekr@rtfm.com): assert here if dtls_ is NULL?
405 return -1;
406 case DTLS_TRANSPORT_CONNECTING:
407 // Can't send data until the connection is active.
408 return -1;
409 case DTLS_TRANSPORT_CONNECTED:
410 if (flags & PF_SRTP_BYPASS) {
411 RTC_DCHECK(!srtp_ciphers_.empty());
412 if (!IsRtpPacket(data, size)) {
413 return -1;
414 }
415
416 return ice_transport_->SendPacket(data, size, options);
417 } else {
418 return (dtls_->WriteAll(data, size, NULL, NULL) == rtc::SR_SUCCESS)
419 ? static_cast<int>(size)
420 : -1;
421 }
422 case DTLS_TRANSPORT_FAILED:
423 // Can't send anything when we're failed.
424 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR)
425 << ToString()
426 << ": Couldn't send packet due to DTLS_TRANSPORT_FAILED.";
427 return -1;
428 case DTLS_TRANSPORT_CLOSED:
429 // Can't send anything when we're closed.
430 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR)
431 << ToString()
432 << ": Couldn't send packet due to DTLS_TRANSPORT_CLOSED.";
433 return -1;
434 default:
435 RTC_NOTREACHED();
436 return -1;
437 }
438}

472void DtlsTransport::ConnectToIceTransport() {
473 RTC_DCHECK(ice_transport_);
474 ice_transport_->SignalWritableState.connect(this,
475 &DtlsTransport::OnWritableState);
476 ice_transport_->SignalReadPacket.connect(this, &DtlsTransport::OnReadPacket);
477 ice_transport_->SignalSentPacket.connect(this, &DtlsTransport::OnSentPacket);
478 ice_transport_->SignalReadyToSend.connect(this,
479 &DtlsTransport::OnReadyToSend);
480 ice_transport_->SignalReceivingState.connect(
481 this, &DtlsTransport::OnReceivingState);
482 ice_transport_->SignalNetworkRouteChanged.connect(
483 this, &DtlsTransport::OnNetworkRouteChanged);
484}
485
486// The state transition logic here is as follows:
487// (1) If we're not doing DTLS-SRTP, then the state is just the
488// state of the underlying impl()
489// (2) If we're doing DTLS-SRTP:
490// - Prior to the DTLS handshake, the state is neither receiving nor
491// writable
492// - When the impl goes writable for the first time we
493// start the DTLS handshake
494// - Once the DTLS handshake completes, the state is that of the
495// impl again
496void DtlsTransport::OnWritableState(rtc::PacketTransportInternal* transport) {
497 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&thread_checker_);
498 RTC_DCHECK(transport == ice_transport_);
499 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE) << ToString()
500 << ": ice_transport writable state changed to "
501 << ice_transport_->writable();
502
503 if (!dtls_active_) {
504 // Not doing DTLS.
505 // Note: SignalWritableState fired by set_writable.
506 set_writable(ice_transport_->writable());
507 return;
508 }
509
510 switch (dtls_state()) {
511 case DTLS_TRANSPORT_NEW:
512 MaybeStartDtls();
513 break;
514 case DTLS_TRANSPORT_CONNECTED:
515 // Note: SignalWritableState fired by set_writable.
516 set_writable(ice_transport_->writable());
517 break;
518 case DTLS_TRANSPORT_CONNECTING:
519 // Do nothing.
520 break;
521 case DTLS_TRANSPORT_FAILED:
522 // Should not happen. Do nothing.
523 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR)
524 << ToString()
525 << ": OnWritableState() called in state DTLS_TRANSPORT_FAILED.";
526 break;
527 case DTLS_TRANSPORT_CLOSED:
528 // Should not happen. Do nothing.
529 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR)
530 << ToString()
531 << ": OnWritableState() called in state DTLS_TRANSPORT_CLOSED.";
532 break;
533 }
534}
535
536void DtlsTransport::OnReceivingState(rtc::PacketTransportInternal* transport) {
537 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&thread_checker_);
538 RTC_DCHECK(transport == ice_transport_);
539 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE) << ToString()
540 << ": ice_transport "
541 "receiving state changed to "
542 << ice_transport_->receiving();
543 if (!dtls_active_ || dtls_state() == DTLS_TRANSPORT_CONNECTED) {
544 // Note: SignalReceivingState fired by set_receiving.
545 set_receiving(ice_transport_->receiving());
546 }
547}
548
549void DtlsTransport::OnReadPacket(rtc::PacketTransportInternal* transport,
550 const char* data,
551 size_t size,
552 const int64_t& packet_time_us,
553 int flags) {
554 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&thread_checker_);
555 RTC_DCHECK(transport == ice_transport_);
556 RTC_DCHECK(flags == 0);
557
558 if (!dtls_active_) {
559 // Not doing DTLS.
560 SignalReadPacket(this, data, size, packet_time_us, 0);
561 return;
562 }
563
564 switch (dtls_state()) {
565 case DTLS_TRANSPORT_NEW:
566 if (dtls_) {
567 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << ToString()
568 << ": Packet received before DTLS started.";
569 } else {
570 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << ToString()
571 << ": Packet received before we know if we are "
572 "doing DTLS or not.";
573 }
574 // Cache a client hello packet received before DTLS has actually started.
575 if (IsDtlsClientHelloPacket(data, size)) {
576 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << ToString()
577 << ": Caching DTLS ClientHello packet until DTLS is "
578 "started.";
579 cached_client_hello_.SetData(data, size);
580 // If we haven't started setting up DTLS yet (because we don't have a
581 // remote fingerprint/role), we can use the client hello as a clue that
582 // the peer has chosen the client role, and proceed with the handshake.
583 // The fingerprint will be verified when it's set.
584 if (!dtls_ && local_certificate_) {
585 SetDtlsRole(rtc::SSL_SERVER);
586 SetupDtls();
587 }
588 } else {
589 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << ToString()
590 << ": Not a DTLS ClientHello packet; dropping.";
591 }
592 break;
593
594 case DTLS_TRANSPORT_CONNECTING:
595 case DTLS_TRANSPORT_CONNECTED:
596 // We should only get DTLS or SRTP packets; STUN's already been demuxed.
597 // Is this potentially a DTLS packet?
598 if (IsDtlsPacket(data, size)) {
599 if (!HandleDtlsPacket(data, size)) {
600 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << ToString() << ": Failed to handle DTLS packet.";
601 return;
602 }
603 } else {
604 // Not a DTLS packet; our handshake should be complete by now.
605 if (dtls_state() != DTLS_TRANSPORT_CONNECTED) {
606 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << ToString()
607 << ": Received non-DTLS packet before DTLS "
608 "complete.";
609 return;
610 }
611
612 // And it had better be a SRTP packet.
613 if (!IsRtpPacket(data, size)) {
614 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR)
615 << ToString() << ": Received unexpected non-DTLS packet.";
616 return;
617 }
618
619 // Sanity check.
620 RTC_DCHECK(!srtp_ciphers_.empty());
621
622 // Signal this upwards as a bypass packet.
623 SignalReadPacket(this, data, size, packet_time_us, PF_SRTP_BYPASS);
624 }
625 break;
626 case DTLS_TRANSPORT_FAILED:
627 case DTLS_TRANSPORT_CLOSED:
628 // This shouldn't be happening. Drop the packet.
629 break;
630 }
631}

635 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&thread_checker_);

645
646void DtlsTransport::OnDtlsEvent(rtc::StreamInterface* dtls, int sig, int err) {
647 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&thread_checker_);
648 RTC_DCHECK(dtls == dtls_.get());
649 if (sig & rtc::SE_OPEN) {
650 // This is the first time.
651 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << ToString() << ": DTLS handshake complete.";
652 if (dtls_->GetState() == rtc::SS_OPEN) {
653 // The check for OPEN shouldn't be necessary but let's make
654 // sure we don't accidentally frob the state if it's closed.
655 set_dtls_state(DTLS_TRANSPORT_CONNECTED);
656 set_writable(true);
657 }
658 }
659 if (sig & rtc::SE_READ) {
660 char buf[kMaxDtlsPacketLen];
661 size_t read;
662 int read_error;
663 rtc::StreamResult ret;
664 // The underlying DTLS stream may have received multiple DTLS records in
665 // one packet, so read all of them.
666 do {
667 ret = dtls_->Read(buf, sizeof(buf), &read, &read_error);
668 if (ret == rtc::SR_SUCCESS) {
669 SignalReadPacket(this, buf, read, rtc::TimeMicros(), 0);
670 } else if (ret == rtc::SR_EOS) {
671 // Remote peer shut down the association with no error.
672 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << ToString() << ": DTLS transport closed by remote";
673 set_writable(false);
674 set_dtls_state(DTLS_TRANSPORT_CLOSED);
675 SignalClosed(this);
676 } else if (ret == rtc::SR_ERROR) {
677 // Remote peer shut down the association with an error.
678 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO)
679 << ToString()
680 << ": Closed by remote with DTLS transport error, code="
681 << read_error;
682 set_writable(false);
683 set_dtls_state(DTLS_TRANSPORT_FAILED);
684 SignalClosed(this);
685 }
686 } while (ret == rtc::SR_SUCCESS);
687 }
688 if (sig & rtc::SE_CLOSE) {
689 RTC_DCHECK(sig == rtc::SE_CLOSE); // SE_CLOSE should be by itself.
690 set_writable(false);
691 if (!err) {
692 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << ToString() << ": DTLS transport closed";
693 set_dtls_state(DTLS_TRANSPORT_CLOSED);
694 } else {
695 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << ToString() << ": DTLS transport error, code=" << err;
696 set_dtls_state(DTLS_TRANSPORT_FAILED);
697 }
698 }
699}
700
701void DtlsTransport::OnNetworkRouteChanged(
702 absl::optional<rtc::NetworkRoute> network_route) {
703 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&thread_checker_);
704 SignalNetworkRouteChanged(network_route);
705}
706
707void DtlsTransport::MaybeStartDtls() {
708 if (dtls_ && ice_transport_->writable()) {
709 ConfigureHandshakeTimeout();
710
711 if (dtls_->StartSSL()) {
712 // This should never fail:
713 // Because we are operating in a nonblocking mode and all
714 // incoming packets come in via OnReadPacket(), which rejects
715 // packets in this state, the incoming queue must be empty. We
716 // ignore write errors, thus any errors must be because of
717 // configuration and therefore are our fault.
718 RTC_NOTREACHED() << "StartSSL failed.";
719 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << ToString() << ": Couldn't start DTLS handshake";
720 set_dtls_state(DTLS_TRANSPORT_FAILED);
721 return;
722 }
723 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << ToString() << ": DtlsTransport: Started DTLS handshake";
724 set_dtls_state(DTLS_TRANSPORT_CONNECTING);
725 // Now that the handshake has started, we can process a cached ClientHello
726 // (if one exists).
727 if (cached_client_hello_.size()) {
728 if (*dtls_role_ == rtc::SSL_SERVER) {
729 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << ToString()
730 << ": Handling cached DTLS ClientHello packet.";
731 if (!HandleDtlsPacket(cached_client_hello_.data<char>(),
732 cached_client_hello_.size())) {
733 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << ToString() << ": Failed to handle DTLS packet.";
734 }
735 } else {
736 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << ToString()
737 << ": Discarding cached DTLS ClientHello packet "
738 "because we don't have the server role.";
739 }
740 cached_client_hello_.Clear();
741 }
742 }
743}
744
745// Called from OnReadPacket when a DTLS packet is received.
746bool DtlsTransport::HandleDtlsPacket(const char* data, size_t size) {
747 // Sanity check we're not passing junk that
748 // just looks like DTLS.
749 const uint8_t* tmp_data = reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(data);
750 size_t tmp_size = size;
751 while (tmp_size > 0) {
752 if (tmp_size < kDtlsRecordHeaderLen)
753 return false; // Too short for the header
754
755 size_t record_len = (tmp_data[11] << 8) | (tmp_data[12]);
756 if ((record_len + kDtlsRecordHeaderLen) > tmp_size)
757 return false; // Body too short
758
759 tmp_data += record_len + kDtlsRecordHeaderLen;
760 tmp_size -= record_len + kDtlsRecordHeaderLen;
761 }
762
763 // Looks good. Pass to the SIC which ends up being passed to
764 // the DTLS stack.
765 return downward_->OnPacketReceived(data, size);
766}

768void DtlsTransport::set_receiving(bool receiving) {
769 if (receiving_ == receiving) {
770 return;
771 }
772 receiving_ = receiving;
773 SignalReceivingState(this);
774}
775
776void DtlsTransport::set_writable(bool writable) {
777 if (writable_ == writable) {
778 return;
779 }
780 if (event_log_) {
781 event_log_->Log(
782 std::make_unique<webrtc::RtcEventDtlsWritableState>(writable));
783 }
784 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE) << ToString() << ": set_writable to: " << writable;
785 writable_ = writable;
786 if (writable_) {
787 SignalReadyToSend(this);
788 }
789 SignalWritableState(this);
790}
791
792void DtlsTransport::set_dtls_state(DtlsTransportState state) {
793 if (dtls_state_ == state) {
794 return;
795 }
796 if (event_log_) {
797 event_log_->Log(std::make_unique<webrtc::RtcEventDtlsTransportState>(
798 ConvertDtlsTransportState(state)));
799 }
800 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE) << ToString() << ": set_dtls_state from:" << dtls_state_
801 << " to " << state;
802 dtls_state_ = state;
803 SendDtlsState(this, state);
804}
805
806void DtlsTransport::OnDtlsHandshakeError(rtc::SSLHandshakeError error) {
807 SendDtlsHandshakeError(error);
808}
809
810void DtlsTransport::ConfigureHandshakeTimeout() {
811 RTC_DCHECK(dtls_);
812 absl::optional<int> rtt = ice_transport_->GetRttEstimate();
813 if (rtt) {
814 // Limit the timeout to a reasonable range in case the ICE RTT takes
815 // extreme values.
816 int initial_timeout = std::max(kMinHandshakeTimeout,
817 std::min(kMaxHandshakeTimeout, 2 * (*rtt)));
818 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << ToString() << ": configuring DTLS handshake timeout "
819 << initial_timeout << " based on ICE RTT " << *rtt;
820
821 dtls_->SetInitialRetransmissionTimeout(initial_timeout);
822 } else {
823 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO)
824 << ToString()
825 << ": no RTT estimate - using default DTLS handshake timeout";
826 }
827}
